					<section>
						<header>
							<h2>External links and Resources</h2>
						</header>
<br>
<section>
<header>
<h3>Data sources</h3>
</header>
<p>
Global climate data - current and past data: <a href="http://www.worldclim.org">Worldclim</a><br>
Global climate data - current and future Data: <a href="https://www.climond.org">Climond</a><br>
Climate prediction Centre  and National Oceanic & Atmospheric Administration climate data:  <a href="http://www.cpc.ncep.noaa.gov">NOAA/CPC</a><br>
Data Distribution Centre (DDC) of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC): <a href="http://www.ipcc-data.org">DDC/IPCC</a><br> 
The Berkeley Erath climate science and strategic analysis project: <a href="http://berkeleyearth.org">Berkeley Earth</a><br>
The New Zealand Land Cover Database: <a href="https://lris.scinfo.org.nz/data">LRIS portal and <a href="https://koordinates.com">koordinates maps</a><br>
NIWA New Zealand climate-related data: <a href="https://www.niwa.co.nz/education-and-training/schools/resources/climate">Climate data and activities</a><br>
Land remote sensing data: <a href="http://landsat.usgs.gov//index.php">Landsat</a><br>
Global biodiveristy information facility: <a href="http://www.gbif.org">GBIF database</a><br>
Crop protection compendium: <a href="http://www.cabi.org/cpc">CABI database</a><br>
Get hourly meteorological data from a station located somewhere on Earth: <a href="http://github.com/rich-iannone/stationaRy">stationaRy</a><br>
Functions to Automate Downloading Geospatial Data Available from Several Federated Data Sources:<a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/FedData/index.html">FedData</a><br></p>
</section>

<section>
<h3>Community & Sharing</h3>
</header>
<p>A network of young modellers in ecology - <a href="http://www.yomos.de">Yomos</a><br>
Platforms for sharing published data and code - <a href="http://github.com/">Github</a>, <a href="http://figshare.com">Figshare</a>, <a href="http://datadryad.org">Datadryad</a>, and <a href="https://plot.ly">Plotly</a><br></p>
</section>
<section>
<header>
<h3>Codes & softwares</h3>
</header>

<p><strong>Niche & Species Distribution Modelling</strong><br>
Species habitat modelling: <a href="http://www.cs.princeton.edu/~schapire/maxent">Maxent</a><br>
Impact of climate change on species distribution: <a href="http://www.hearne.software/Software/CLIMEX-DYMEX/Editions">Climex</a><br>
Functions for species distribution modeling with R: <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/dismo/index.html">dismo</a><br>
Tools for processing data associated with species distribution modelling exercises with R: <a href="http://www.rdocumentation.org/packages/SDMTools">SDMTools</a><br>
Ensemble platform for species distribution modeling with R: <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/packages/biomod2/index.html">biomod2</a><br>
Bayesian species distribution modeling with R: <a href="http://hsdm.sourceforge.net">hSDM</a><br>
Uncertainty analysis for species distribution models with R: <a href="https://www.rdocumentation.org/packages/usdm">usdm</a><br>
<br>
<strong>Indivdiual based Spread Modelling</strong><br>
Modular dispersal framework (MDiG) for modelling the spread of invasive species integrated in GIS: <a href="https://github.com/ferrouswheel/mdig">MDiG</a><br>
Spatially-explicit demographic niche modelling in R: <a href="http://demoniche.r-forge.r-project.org/">Demoniche</a><br>
<br>
<strong>Spatio-Temporal analysis</strong><br>
Check CRAN Task View on <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/views/Spatial.html">Spatial</a> and <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/views/SpatioTemporal.html">Spatiotemporal</a> data<br>
Check also CRAN Task View on <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/views/WebTechnologies.html">Web technologies</a> for access to many GIS data<br>
Methods for working with weather & climate data in R: <a href="https://rforge.net/doc/packages/climates/00Index.html">Climates</a><br>
R functions for working with station and gridded climate data: <a href="http://rpackages.ianhowson.com/rforge/climstats">climstats</a><br>
Neutral landscape modelling: <a href="http://www.umces.edu/al/program/gardner/Qrule">Qrule</a>, <a href="http://www.simmap.com/">SIMMAP</a>, <a href="https://pypi.python.org/pypi/nlmpy">python-based NLMpy package</a><br>
Time Series Analysis and Mining with R:  <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/views/TimeSeries.html">Cran Task view</a> and <a href="http://www.rdatamining.com">RDataMining</a><br>
Spatial analyses of biodiversity: <a href="https://github.com/shawnlaffan/biodiverse">biodiverse</a><br>
Measuring the variety of nature & selecting priority areas for conservation: <a href="http://www.nhm.ac.uk/research-curation/research/projects/worldmap/siteplan.htm">Biodiversity and WorldMap </a><br>
<br>
<strong>Phylogenetics, phylogeography & comparative analysis</strong><br>
Check CRAN Task View on <a href="https://cran.r-project.org/web/views/Phylogenetics.html">Phylogenetics</a><br>
<br></p></section>

		
</div>
